seed_chunks:
Beneath the bruise-violet night, three powers annotate the world in competing hands. The **Candlelit Concord**—monks, lantern-scribes, and wardens of “safe” lore—publicly offers sanctuaries and careful catalogues, yet secretly culls pages that predict revolt, hunting the Midnight Atlas to lock it in a reliquary. The **Grave-Gild Syndicate** presents itself as respectable undertakers and memorial artisans, but traffics in desire-ink distilled from the dead, bribing Concord clerks and commissioning forgeries to steer inheritances and hauntings. Threading between them, the **Mothlight Cartographers** pose as harmless wandering mapmakers, while covertly stitching a living map of buried longings to awaken a sleeping city beneath the mausoleums—sabotaging Syndicate ledgers and stealing Concord lamplight.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Candlelit Concord",
      "public_front": "Monastic librarians, lantern-scribes, and wardens who provide sanctuaries, catalogues, and protective rites against the uncanny.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Suppress prophetic or destabilizing texts by excising pages and imprisoning dangerous knowledge; seek the Midnight Atlas to seal it away permanently."
    },
    {
      "name": "Grave-Gild Syndicate",
      "public_front": "Respectable undertakers, memorial artists, and mausoleum caretakers who manage burials and keep the dead 'at rest.'",
      "hidden_agenda": "Harvest and trade desire-ink from the dead to manipulate the living (inheritances, loyalties, hauntings); bribe Concord scribes and fund Atlas forgeries."
    },
    {
      "name": "Mothlight Cartographers",
      "public_front": "Wandering mapmakers and wayfinders who sell routes through ruins, graveyards, and mushroom rings to travelers.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Secretly stitch a living map of buried longings to awaken a city beneath the mausoleums; steal Concord lamplight and sabotage Syndicate records to prevent control."
    }
  ]
}
```

Mothlight has begun to fall like ash over the Old Necropolis, and with it the **Mothlight Cartographers** are sewing a “route” straight through sealed mausoleums—each new stitch waking hungry epitaph-spirits and collapsing honest paths into looping script. In response, the **Candlelit Concord** declares a dusk curfew and dispatches Warden-Scribes to confiscate lamps and “unsafe” notes, including Eldra Quillwhisper’s satchel if found. Meanwhile the **Grave-Gild Syndicate** hosts a lavish Vigil-Auction of desire-ink, selling forged Atlas-leaves that provoke fresh hauntings when read aloud.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "The Stitched Route Through Seals",
      "description": "Mothlight Cartographers are stitching a living path across the Old Necropolis, forcing entry through warded mausoleums; the route rearranges itself into looping script and rouses epitaph-spirits that feed on unfinished grief.",
      "tensions": [
        "Travel becomes unreliable; roads rewrite and strand pilgrims in repeating corridors",
        "Angered dead spill into nearby districts, blaming whoever carries lamplight",
        "Cartographers risk exposure and retaliation if caught with stolen Concord wick-oil"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Curfew of the Candle and the Vigil-Auction",
      "description": "The Candlelit Concord imposes a dusk curfew and sends Warden-Scribes to seize lamps, journals, and suspect pages, while the Grave-Gild Syndicate runs a secret Vigil-Auction selling desire-ink and forged Midnight Atlas leaves that trigger hauntings when recited.",
      "tensions": [
        "Concord raids endanger innocents and independent scribes—Eldra’s warded papers are prime targets",
        "Syndicate forgeries muddy all leads to the true Atlas and incite lethal, misdirected hauntings",
        "Bribed clerks and double agents spark paranoia within all three factions"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

